<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 10:14PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Scotland,
southeastern Richmond and southern Hoke Counties through 1115 PM
EDT...
At 1014 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurinburg, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and heavy rainfall up to 1.5
inches.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Raeford, Hoffman, Antioch, Wagram, Gibson, East
Laurinburg, Laurel Hill, Sandhills Game Land and Rockfish.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
